The protecting lairies ol the knights, the giant persecutors ol ludier, the enchanters, the magio, and all those illusions are the imits of that brilliant and dreamy imagination which characterizes the modern Orientals. We have enthusiasti- cally enjoyed them in the depths ol the barbarity where we were plunged; we have allowed ourselves to be drawn by the charms ol rhyme, like children in the cradle whom their nurses put to slcep by the monotonous sound oi a lullaby.
